<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4647091>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 5. Lophiobrycon weitzmani, paratype, alizarin stained pectoral fin of adult male, ventral view, anteriormost fin ray at top, medial fin ray at bottom. Arrow indicates modified portions of the lepidotrichia supporting the diagnostic globular expansion, formed by the lepidotrichia and hypertrophied soft tissue (not represented in the illustration), in the middle portions of the unbranched (above) and first branched (below) pectoral-fin rays. LIRP 4338, 24.7 mm SL, same locality data as in Figs. 1 and 3." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4647091/files/figure.png" .

